Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.47,0:00:03.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1}{\fnArial Black\pos(316,325)\fad(800,0)}Obey the Rules and manners\Nto have a fun Duel!!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.43,0:00:16.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Worried that this full tank of energy will lose it's destination
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.74,0:00:22.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Whoever shakes for just a minute their boredom, will explode!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.87,0:00:28.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I ride, atop the white line, Oh, Oh, Oh
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.96,0:00:34.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Sit down, in the place you have faith Oh, Oh, Oh
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.97,0:00:38.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Go to the place that tempts you!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.30,0:00:44.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If each person took one thing at a time, freedom and passion in their hand
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.56,0:00:50.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}For the shine to come, continue our journey
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.69,0:00:56.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The unclear everyday trump-card that sustains me, is your soul
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.91,0:01:02.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The best growth is coming forth, unstoppable wild drive
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.91,0:01:08.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We are both yet to settle down, striking the door
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.91,0:01:43.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now it's {\i1}your{\i0} turn, Malik!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.91,0:01:45.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Card draw.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.87,0:01:49.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on! Hurry it up!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.67,0:01:52.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what you do, the outcome of this match is within sight!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.42,0:02:01.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On my next turn, you're gonna be killed by your own Winged Sun Dragon of Ra! Thus bringing this farce to its end!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.93,0:02:05.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You're not the only one who can read the Hieratic Text!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.35,0:02:10.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll bury you in darkness next turn with the Winged Sun Dragon of Ra!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.31,0:02:15.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's quite {\i1}bold{\i0} of you, Dominant Half...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.19,0:02:19.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I don't think I can even {\i1}call{\i0} you "Dominant Half" anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.32,0:02:20.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.95,0:02:26.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I took the Millennium Rod from the Ishtar family, who guarded it for centuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.29,0:02:28.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It now lies in {\i1}my{\i0} hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.12,0:02:32.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This is {\b0}mine{\b1} from now on.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.88,0:02:38.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Rod accepted {\i1}me{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.13,0:02:41.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In order to allow {\i1}me{\i0} to help {\i1}you{\i0} with your revenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.14,0:02:46.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So it just might be {\i1}me{\i0}\N who's the dominant half!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.39,0:02:47.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Screw you!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.68,0:02:49.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1\b0}I{\b1} am Malik Ishtar!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.98,0:02:53.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Very well, forget it...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.65,0:02:58.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're gonna Summon Ra,\N go on and do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.36,0:03:00.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our answer will be here soon...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.74,0:03:03.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate the Magic Card,\N Vengeful Bog Spirit!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.37,0:03:12.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to this card's effect, all Monsters on the field cannot attack within the turn they are Summoned.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.88,0:03:14.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn over!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.00,0:03:20.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whether I attack with Ra in the first turn or the second, the result's still the same!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.01,0:03:21.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.63,0:03:22.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Go, Bakura!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.93,0:03:24.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Go on and Summon Ra!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.93,0:03:26.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't bother me!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.52,0:03:30.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Prepare yourself, Malik.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.68,0:03:34.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna play your\N beloved Ra right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.27,0:03:37.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I sacrifice every Monster I have on the field, totaling three tributes!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.03,0:03:41.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come forth! Winged Sun Dragon of Ra!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.16,0:03:44.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You {\i1}fell{\i0} for it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.53,0:03:47.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate the Trap Card, Joyful Doom!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.41,0:03:50.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.58,0:03:53.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to the effect of Joyful Doom,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.21,0:03:58.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Attack Points of the Monsters you tributed are added to my Life Points!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.59,0:04:01.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the Attack Power of every Monster you just sacrificed...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.84,0:04:03.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...drops to {\i1}0{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.20,0:04:31.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.25,0:04:33.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Winged Sun Dragon of Ra has 0 Attack Points?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.75,0:04:39.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Ra's Attack Power is determined by the total Attack Points of the Monsters sacrificed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.88,0:04:44.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If the Monsters sacrificed to Summon it have 0 Attack Points, then {\b0}Ra{\b1}'s Attack Power...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.72,0:04:46.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}will be 0!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.47,0:04:47.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell do you mean?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.68,0:04:49.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's different from\N what you told me before!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.68,0:04:53.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I never had a\N card like that in my deck!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.73,0:04:54.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shit...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.85,0:04:58.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He planned on us stealing the Winged Sun Dragon of Ra...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.36,0:05:00.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So he baited us with it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.03,0:05:06.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even more, his Life Points rose all the way up to 8550!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.07,0:05:07.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shit...!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.12,0:05:11.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I switch both the Winged Sun Dragon of Ra and the Puppet Master into Defense Position!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.22,0:05:27.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? I...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.01,0:05:29.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...was in Mai-{\i1}san{\i0}'s room before, the last I remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.89,0:05:31.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Where is...?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.77,0:05:38.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.81,0:05:40.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's me! Anzu!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.98,0:05:42.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anzu...?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.44,0:05:46.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.95,0:05:48.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So late at night...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.53,0:05:51.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bakura-{\i1}kun{\i0}... Bakura-{\i1}kun{\i0}'s gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.83,0:05:59.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.00,0:06:00.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Card draw.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.59,0:06:04.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here I come, Bakura...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.76,0:06:07.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Drillago, attack the Puppet Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.27,0:06:18.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Puppet Master is beaten!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.98,0:06:21.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I end my turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.81,0:06:23.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.90,0:06:25.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Card draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.32,0:06:28.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All you've got left\N is that 0 Attack Power Ra!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.65,0:06:30.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you plan to do {\i1}now{\i0}, Bakura?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.32,0:06:33.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't a joke...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.08,0:06:36.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't need a god\N with 0 Attack Points!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.58,0:06:39.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I sacrifice the Winged Sun Dragon of Ra!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.96,0:06:49.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To Summon\N Hades, Ruler of the Realm of the Dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.64,0:06:57.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe you\N cast God aside so easily...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.23,0:07:06.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You must have the Resurrection of the Dead\N you stole from me in your hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.36,0:07:07.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.11,0:07:17.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ra's Attack and Defense Points are determined by the total Attack and Defense Points of the three Monsters used to Summon it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.16,0:07:24.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, if God is Summoned using Resurrection of the Dead without any sacrifices, its Attack Points will be 0!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.59,0:07:28.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So Ra's {\i1}better off{\i0} in the Graveyard!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.97,0:07:34.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's true that the Winged Sun Dragon of Ra should now be sealed off entirely.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.93,0:07:38.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But why do I feel like he's got something up his sleeve?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.72,0:07:40.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why is he standing there unfazed?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.27,0:07:43.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I failed in Summoning Ra,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.56,0:07:46.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but my turn is {\i1}far{\i0} from over!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.03,0:07:52.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll tribute 3 Demon-type Monsters in my Graveyard from play!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.53,0:07:55.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To Summon Dark Necrofear!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.37,0:08:06.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then, the Magic Card Early Burial!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.42,0:08:09.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I pay 800 of my Life...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.09,0:08:12.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...to revive Ghost Duke\N from the Graveyard!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.30,0:08:20.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My deck only gets {\i1}stronger{\i0} when you send Monsters to the Graveyard!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.22,0:08:23.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Knock it off! If we lose any more Life Points, we're in trouble!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.23,0:08:27.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up! I thought I told you you not to bother me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.94,0:08:32.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we want to reduce his Life at all, it's necessary to take risks!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.95,0:08:34.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Just calm down, Bakura!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.32,0:08:36.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He's still planning something.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.57,0:08:37.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I know myself all too well!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.49,0:08:40.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell do {\i1}you{\i0} know?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.70,0:08:45.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And now that I think about it, Malik, it's {\i1}your{\i0} fault our previous strategy didn't work!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.62,0:08:46.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What'd you say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.21,0:08:48.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Get the hell outta me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.38,0:08:50.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fighting amongst one another...?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.42,0:08:53.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not that I mind it,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.05,0:08:55.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but let's continue the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.09,0:08:59.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Any Monster Summoned this turn...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.05,0:09:02.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...cannot attack due to the effect of Vengeful Bog Spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.93,0:09:06.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know that without\N you needing to tell me!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.10,0:09:07.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn end!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.23,0:09:08.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's just continue this already!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.90,0:09:10.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Really{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.19,0:09:12.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then allow me to\N get things moving again.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.82,0:09:14.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.36,0:09:15.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.70,0:09:21.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder where Bakura-{\i1}kun{\i0} ran off to...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.60,0:09:25.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He couldn't walk alone with his body like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.47,0:09:29.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe Malik did something to Bakura-{\i1}kun{\i0} again...!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.51,0:09:40.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll create a simulation depicting the outcome of my Virus Combo's success...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.70,0:09:46.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}There's only a 13% chance of the Virus Combo working on the Ra Deck!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.36,0:09:52.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell are you laughing at?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.78,0:09:55.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One Turn Kill...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.44,0:09:56.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.90,0:10:00.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're going to {\i1}die{\i0}\N in just one turn, Bakura!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.70,0:10:01.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What'd you say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.41,0:10:06.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even my dominant half doesn't know about this...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.21,0:10:09.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll show you the second hidden Special Ability of Ra!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.96,0:10:14.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Ra's Special Ability that\N I don't know about?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.76,0:10:17.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One Turn Kill?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.44,0:10:37.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One Turn Kill...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.37,0:10:45.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}When the conditions are\N right for the Ra card,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.12,0:10:50.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}in {\b0}one turn{\b1}, it can crush all its enemies and reduce the player's Life Points to 0...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.34,0:10:57.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The three God Cards...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.01,0:11:00.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The one I hold,\N Great War God Obelisk...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.72,0:11:03.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi's Osiris the Heaven Dragon...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.39,0:11:05.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And Malik's Winged Sun Dragon of Ra...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.14,0:11:11.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The one thing they have in common is that they are Summoned to the field with three sacrifices.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.77,0:11:15.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And most Trap Cards\N have no effect on them...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.82,0:11:18.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Magic Cards used on them are only effective for one turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.99,0:11:25.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But there is one Ability Ra has that the others don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.24,0:11:28.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The power of {\b0}quickness{\b1}!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.13,0:11:47.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Magic Cards only affect a God Card for one turn, whether the cards are yours or your enemy's...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.31,0:11:51.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Therefore, the effects of Resurrection of the Dead will expire after just one turn,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.52,0:11:53.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and will once again\N return to the Graveyard...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.36,0:12:00.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And thanks to the effects of my Vengeful Bog Spirit Magic Card, it won't be able to attack in the turn I Summon it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.57,0:12:05.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But... Ra has the power\N to attack {\b0}instantly{\b1}!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.87,0:12:08.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One turn is more than enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.91,0:12:12.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I activate Ra's Hidden Special Ability,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.16,0:12:14.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you'll be finished in an {\i1}instant{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.71,0:12:20.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If the Ra card goes to the Graveyard...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.88,0:12:23.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...and you have the Resurrection of the Dead in your hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.22,0:12:27.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The One Turn Kill is complete!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.44,0:12:36.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, Yugi!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.65,0:12:38.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's...!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.02,0:12:39.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not just fog!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.11,0:12:43.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the Void of Darkness where Dark Games are played!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.57,0:12:45.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then that means Bakura-{\i1}kun{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.25,0:12:57.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bakura must be playing a Dark Game inside there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.33,0:12:59.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And his opponent has to be Malik.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.09,0:13:01.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anzu, don't get too close.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.21,0:13:03.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'd be best off\N returning to your room.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.09,0:13:04.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.05,0:13:05.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anzu!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.30,0:13:09.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're always excluding me when there's an emergency!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.10,0:13:16.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like I don't know anything about the Millennium Items, you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.10,0:13:20.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I also know all about your lost memories, other Yugi...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.07,0:13:23.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anzu...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.49,0:13:26.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to help you out, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.66,0:13:36.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Playtime's over.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.62,0:13:40.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm about to send you {\i1}both{\i0} to the World of Darkness!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.67,0:13:43.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate a Magic Card from my hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.76,0:13:46.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Resurrection of the Dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.18,0:13:53.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And of {\i1}course{\i0}, the one I Special Summon to the field...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.06,0:13:54.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...is the Winged Sun Dragon of Ra!!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.36,0:14:10.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But because it wasn't a Sacrifice Summon, its Attack and Defense Points should be 0!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.20,0:14:13.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Plus, Resurrection of the Dead only works for one turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.29,0:14:16.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If we can survive this turn, God should disappear!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.50,0:14:22.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll see about that...\N You don't understand the true power of Ra!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.80,0:14:27.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What the hell...?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.34,0:14:28.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's he doing...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.59,0:14:29.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm not sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.68,0:14:33.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This is the first time I've heard this Hieratic Text...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.36,0:14:46.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My dominant half never received the full revelation of the Millennium Rod...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.94,0:14:50.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Only I can decipher God's Special Ability!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.41,0:14:55.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.41,0:14:58.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Malik's body is disappearing!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.04,0:15:00.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll tell you...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.33,0:15:02.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ra's Special Ability...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.71,0:15:05.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As written on the card\N in Hieratic Text:
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.88,0:15:08.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"He who chants the third litany...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.47,0:15:12.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...may keep 1 Life Point and transfer the remainder
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.72,0:15:16.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,unto Ra's Attack Points for one turn!"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.22,0:15:22.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The player's Life Points change into Ra's Attack and Defense Points?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.94,0:15:24.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.69,0:15:26.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And it doesn't take any time at all...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.07,0:15:29.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's been a fun little Duel, Bakura.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.78,0:15:33.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the last time you'll see me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.41,0:15:37.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But once you disappear into darkness, my body will go back to normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.95,0:15:39.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.30,0:15:52.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Ra's Special Ability!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.05,0:15:54.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ra and I become one!!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.60,0:16:02.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He fused with Ra?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.60,0:16:03.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ra, attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.65,0:16:06.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,God Blaze Cannon!!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.91,0:16:17.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Destroy every Monster!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.58,0:16:24.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And kill the player!!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.04,0:16:30.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now die, my residual thoughts!!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.01,0:16:41.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My lost memory as the Pharaoh...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.56,0:16:45.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's not much I know about it myself...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.06,0:16:48.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I must obtain it at all costs!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.65,0:16:51.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what\N kind of memory it may be.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.65,0:16:56.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I no longer want to put everyone in danger because of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.54,0:17:04.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.50,0:17:12.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll let you win this time...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.13,0:17:15.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those are some brave words...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.55,0:17:17.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But remember this!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.59,0:17:19.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be resurrected in due time!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.97,0:17:21.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To {\i1}kill{\i0} you!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.81,0:17:24.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I {\i1}originated{\i0} from the darkness anyway!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.33,0:17:43.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The darkness, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.08,0:17:48.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I'll enjoy {\i1}taming{\i0} the darkness...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.96,0:17:49.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Malik!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.55,0:17:53.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So {\i1}you{\i0} came here, Yugi?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.34,0:17:55.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where did you send Bakura?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.68,0:17:57.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Bakura{\i0}, you mean...?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.97,0:17:58.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.97,0:18:03.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody {\i1}knows{\i0} where those who lose a Dark Game are sent!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.02,0:18:05.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bakura lost?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.73,0:18:08.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi! It'll be {\i1}your{\i0} turn very soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.40,0:18:10.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then you can reunite with Bakura in the {\i1}next world{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.79,0:18:27.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Sister!!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.54,0:18:31.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Malik...!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.97,0:18:38.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're...?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.93,0:18:40.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My sister...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.80,0:18:42.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Big sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.47,0:18:43.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Rishid...!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.89,0:18:44.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Malik!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.93,0:18:47.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Save Rishid from that man!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.82,0:19:00.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe the Parasite Mind I used a while back would come in handy {\i1}now{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.16,0:19:08.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The Millennium Ring's power lets one seal part of their own soul within an object!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.08,0:19:09.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That includes this piece of the Puzzle!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.59,0:19:14.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Parasite Mind!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.96,0:19:16.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Seal complete!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.13,0:19:19.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The moment Malik's attack killed me...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.63,0:19:22.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...I suddenly woke up inside of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.01,0:19:26.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Can't be helped.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.52,0:19:29.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll sit tight and wait for the Millennium Items to be gathered,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.52,0:19:34.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and begin my search for the "Door of Truth" which lies somewhere inside of here...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.08,0:19:53.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where the hell did he {\i1}go{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.38,0:20:04.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}An invincible God Card that decides the match in just one turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.68,0:20:07.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Is there any way to stand up to Ra?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.36,0:20:17.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Big brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.52,0:20:19.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're still up?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.15,0:20:22.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should go to bed.\N Tomorrow's the Finals!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.86,0:20:23.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.99,0:20:24.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.87,0:20:26.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Big brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.96,0:20:40.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The place we're headed for is Alcatraz.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.38,0:20:45.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our stepfather, Gozaburo Kaiba, spent a fortune building that island.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.47,0:20:48.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was full of high-tech\N military equipment.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.52,0:20:51.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}After he died,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.68,0:20:53.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}my brother destroyed\N all of the facilities,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.85,0:20:56.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and built the\N Duel Tower atop the ruins.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.06,0:20:58.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mokuba...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.11,0:21:01.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will win the Finals\N on Alcatraz Island!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.15,0:21:04.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And when I earn\N the title of Duel King,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.61,0:21:07.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will finally obtain true victory!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.03,0:21:12.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Only when that happens will I be freed of his curse!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.50,0:21:20.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If my hunch is right...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.42,0:21:22.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...there {\i1}is{\i0} a way to overcome Ra!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.17,0:21:26.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait for me, final stage of our last battle! Alcatraz!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.05,0:21:29.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will become the true Duel King,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.85,0:21:32.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and conquer the future!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.98,0:21:39.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(140,141)}"Preview"
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.82,0:21:40.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh no!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.48,0:21:45.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Battle Ship suddenly changes its route on the way to the destination of the Finals!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.40,0:21:47.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Some unknown person seizes control of the ship,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.99,0:21:49.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but who could even do that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.99,0:21:54.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then out of nowhere, a giant mobile fortress submerges from the water!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.33,0:21:55.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the heck {\i1}is{\i0} that thing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.46,0:21:56.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And who are {\i1}they{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.92,0:21:59.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've never heard of such a thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.46,0:22:00.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.17,0:22:03.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Unknown Challenger:\N The Huge Mobile Fortress Submerges!"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.59,0:22:05.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Duel standby!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.08,0:22:14.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The unsinkable sun, wherever it rises
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.96,0:22:23.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A dream is a dream, and it won't stop
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.26,0:22:28.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The straight rail and the steep route
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.89,0:22:33.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}To go, or not go all of yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.27,0:22:40.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm getting tired of counting my advances in a cage
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.82,0:22:44.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Respect! Boys, show me your strength
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.41,0:22:49.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's awkward, but draw the map
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.16,0:22:59.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Now let's walk forever with our head up high...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.25,0:23:07.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The unsinkable sun, if it starts to get to familiar like you
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.14,0:23:15.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}answer freely to the everyday discomfort
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.85,0:23:23.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I want to believe you, because I am losing my way with everything
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.82,0:23:33.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Hiding in my heart... this secret paradise
